FL,379,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37805
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F378A1784225905
OL,3,CFirst lowland tapir calf born in 14
OL,4,Cyears at Hertfordshire Zoo
OL,6,FIn the wild, the stripes and spots
OL,7,Fprovide vital camouflage by mimicking
OL,8,Fthe dappled light of the rainforest
OL,9,Ffloor.
OL,11,FThe distinctive pattern will gradually
OL,12,Ffade over the coming months as the
OL,13,Fcalf develops its adult coat.
OL,15,FOften referred to as the 'gardeners of
OL,16,Fthe forest', tapirs play a critical
OL,17,Frole in maintaining healthy ecosystems
OL,18,Fthrough seed dispersal.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G5/5
